<paragraph blockId="11.[315,1707,414,778]" pageId="11" pageNumber="294">
Remarks: A species related to both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ricardo." authorityYear="1925" baseAuthorityName="Ricardo" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[1040,1110,667,694]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Daspletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtus">
<emphasis box="[1040,1110,667,694]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="294">hirtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Londt" authorityYear="1983" box="[1203,1314,672,694]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Daspietis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stenoura">
<emphasis box="[1203,1314,672,694]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="294">stenoura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but easily distinguished on male genital structure. Females are difficult to separate but 
<emphasis box="[1356,1471,707,743]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="294">placodes</emphasis>
has dark redbrown tibiae and tarsi.
</paragraph>
